at|
When you have 7 cards between you and partner. Missing 6 (an even number) MOST of the time they will divide BADLY
Missing an ODD number, they will divide favourably|
pg| ***** 31 ***** |


lc|cak287643|nt||at|
Thus we should expect diamonds (missing 6 of them) to divide 4-2.
BUT clubs we have 8...missing 5, they will divide 3-2 more often
(an odd number missing tends to split more evenly)
Thus, clubs should be your project suit|
